<hl>
<seg id=1> Thinking discriminated by the natives, thousands of British immigrants leave Australia </seg>
</hl>
<p>
<seg id=2> (Sydney, AFP) A survey issued yesterday shows that because of "British-hating" psychology and the discrimination from the native people, thousands of British immigrants decide to leave Australia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=3> For the interest of the immigrants to that area and ecnomic interest of Australia, the British Immigrants Association calls on the government to take the issue seriously. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=4> The chairman of the Association, Hunter pointed out that, the Britons think that the Australians have "British-hating" psychology, and the Australia economy may lose several million for it. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=5> He said that so many British immigrants choose to leave Australia is really distressing, for those who leave are almost ecnomically independent skilled labors. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=6> He told reporters: "According to the immigration rules here, these immigrants are not the kind that you want to toss off." </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=7> Immigrants from Britain accounts for 14% of the total immigration population of Australia. </seg>
<seg id=8> Nevertheness, statistics from the immigration office shows that, from 1996 to 1997, 11,978 British new immigrants came to Australia, and 3,737 left the country at the same time. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=9> Hunter said, the Association found through independent surveys that about one fourth of the Britons believe they are discriminated in Australia. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=10> Almost 40% that questioned think the local people take sides with those of non-British origin. </seg>
<seg id=11> 37% said that complaints from British immigrants won't be take as seriously as those from other nationalities. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=12> About 35% of them blame the media be responsible for the prejudice of the local people to the British immigrants. </seg>
</p>
<p>
<seg id=13> Hunter said that former Australian Prime Minister Keating's anti-British position plays no good role in this issue. </seg>
</p>
